  <a href="#1" id="1">
   The Senate panel considering John Tower's nomination as Secretary of Defense has found discrepancies in his dealings with defense contractors.
  </a>
  <a href="#2" id="2">
   The panel members cited differences in his testimony before the group
  </a>
  <a href="#3" id="3">
   and what he wrote in a deposition given at the time of his divorce from his second wife in 1987.
  </a>
  <a href="#4" id="4">
   Tower had told the panel that he only represented British Aerospace, Inc. on matters of civil aviation.
  </a>
  <a href="#5" id="5">
   In the deposition, however, he wrote that he had given the company advice on selling certain systems to the defense department.
  </a>
  <a href="#6" id="6">
   The panel also is concerned about Tower's drinking habits and reports of womanizing.
  </a>
